<br>
Example: I have my healer (shammy in this case) parked at a camp spot safe from roamers and send my monk out to pull...  There are 3 mobs in the room I want to pull so I aggro one, run a little bit and FD...  Two of the 3 are casters and nuke me to half health before I get my FD off...  I run my healer up, outside of normal aggro range, and cast heal on the apparantly dead monk while the mobs are standing over him...  Will that cause them to aggro the healer and smash her pretty little face into a fine white paste?<br>
<br>
I have yet to try this with my little 2 box pair as I'm afraid it will lead to my healer's demise...<br>
<br>
 <p>Zonker <br>
<font color="yellow">53</font>rd Champion of Vision...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ussyxz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ssyxz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 381<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/11/02 3:57:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1874.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Healing the dead... (aggro question)</span><hr size=1> Nope, doesn't lead to aggro.<br>
<br>
 <p><center><b>Ssyxz<br>58 Iksar Master<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=178226">Magelo</a></b</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 4024<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/11/02 4:15:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1874.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Healing the dead... (aggro question)</span><hr size=1> In your example, no it won't.<br>
<br>
If the heal is started before the feign, and lands after the feign, then it would. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tarrask>Tarrask</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/12/02 5:12:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1874.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Healing the dead... (aggro question)</span><hr size=1> Heal on a succesfully FD'd monk gains no aggro.  <br>
<br>
Start a heal before FD, and you'll get aggro.  Heal a monk who stands before the heal lands, you'll get aggro.  Heal a monk who gets his FD broken by a spell, you'll get aggro.<br>
<br>
Basically FD the monk, be sure it has worked, then and only then heal him.<br>
<br>
Same principle applies to raids.  I have had 2 raids wipeout because one healer or another didn't wait for me to call for a heal. <p>Tarrask, 51st Swifttail of Saryrn
<BR>
<BR>
Do not walk before me, for I may not follow.  Do not walk behind me, for I may not lead.  Do not walk beside me either, just leave me the hell alone. <BR>
<BR>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231234/" target="_blank"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uz0nk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Z0nk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/12/02 7:31:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1874.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Healing the dead... (aggro question)</span><hr size=1> Thanks for your replys...<br>
<br>
Since this is my 2box pair I have less to worry about the healer screwing it up as I can be sure that the FD works before I cast the heal...<br>
<br>
I have learned the hard way that it's much better to save one of the characters rather than get wiped out so if the FD fails, its better the just let the monk die rather than try and save him with a heal that will kill the healer and likely the monk as well... Just as much, its better to FD the monk if I get an unexpected add that I cannot handle and let the healer take one for the team...  Somehow a death is much less harsh if I know that I saved one of my toons... <p>Zonker <br>
<font color="yellow">53</font>rd Champion of Vision...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utulanehaiwae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tulane HaiWae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 326<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/17/02 2:18:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1874.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Healing the dead... (aggro question)</span><hr size=1> At level 30 a cleric friend and i went down to upper guk Ancient Crocodile camp to get him some legs and me both pieces if they dropped.  He (being a dwarf) was not KOS to the live frogs, and intended to stay that way, so that he coul dtravel to lower guk safely later on in life.  Since as an iksar i started out KOS, i didn't mind losing faction with the live side.  <br>
<br>
What we did was, since the AC spawn is a 28 (?) min spawn, we would both kill that (no faction hit) then i would go out and pull trains of live mobs back to the AC camp.  I would pick them off and kill them one by one, and every time i needed a heal i would FD and make sure agro was clear, and the non-kos cleric standing right next to me would toss me a heal.  I would then get back up and back to fighting.. we ended up spending all of level 30 (roughly 6 hours i believe) exping here and got all the gatorscale armor we could handle.. and the cleric still wasnt KOS..<br>
<br>
So the moral of the story.. Yes you can heal someone who is fully and properly feigned, and it will not transfer agro to you. <p><center>
<br><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47550">Assid Reflux</a></b></center>
